        <p class="note" MadCap:autonum="&lt;b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #fdc80b;&quot; class=&quot;mcFormatColor&quot;&gt;Note &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;">If you click inside a paragraph (rather than at the very beginning) and press <span class="Emphasis"><MadCap:keyword term="Tabs" />Tab</span> or click <img src="../../../../Images/Shared/Co-Fl/Interface/Buttons/Indent-Items-btn.png" class="ReduceButtonSize" /> in the Home ribbon or Text Format toolabar, you will notice that the paragraph is not indented, but rather the Create Group dialog opens, allowing you to select different types of block styles. These styles let you create block-level content in a unique "container" for different purposes.  <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Flare-Online-Only">See <MadCap:xref href="../../../../../Flare/Styles/Other-Features-Activities/Regular-Stylesheets/Styles/Creating-Divs-Tag-Groups.htm">Creating Divs and Other Tag Groups</MadCap:xref>. </MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Contributor">See <MadCap:xref href="../../../../../Contributor/Styles/More/Creating-Tag-Groups.htm">Creating Tag Groups</MadCap:xref>. </MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="General.Print-Only">For more information about tag groups, see the online Help.</MadCap:conditionalText></p>
